  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting Transitional Justice, Community-Based Reintegration and Economic Recovery in the Context of Spontaneous Surrenders in Kasai, Kasai Central and Tanganyika Provinces of the Democratic Republic of the Congo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A needs assessment identified the lack of reintegration support for spontaneously surrendered former combatants of local militias, returning displaced populations, at risk youth and vulnerable populations as a key impediment to sustainable peace, reconciliation, and confict management by the Government in the Democratic Republic of Congo. To address these challenges, this project supports transitional justice activities coupled with community-based reintegration and efforts to revitalize local economies under a consortium consisting of UNDP (lead), the MONUSCO Joint Human Rights Office (JHRO) and IOM. In particular, through this project, IOM works on these much-needed peacebuilding processes as well as to engage with other donors to ensure a more longer-term investment in stabilization in the target areas.</narrative>
  </description>
